  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/4521",
  "title": "Searching for facet can throw an error when a refinement list is expanded with more than 100 items.",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\nSearching for facet can throw an error when a refinement list is expanded with more than 100 items.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://codesandbox.io/s/admiring-haslett-ipfw1?file=/src/app.js\r\n2. Click on \"Show more\" button on the refinement list\r\n3. Type any key on the facet search bar\r\n4. See error\r\n\r\n## The problematic configuration\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\r\n    container: '#brand-list',\r\n    attribute: 'brand',\r\n    searchable: true,\r\n    limit: 10,\r\n    showMore: true,\r\n    showMoreLimit: 1000,\r\n  }),\r\n```\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWe should be able to search. Although we have `showMoreLimit: 1000`, facet search shouldn't use `1000` as is. We should cap it (probably to 100?).\r\n\r\n## 🖥 Screenshots\r\n\r\n<!-- If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem. -->\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/499898/93888367-3630c700-fce8-11ea-9023-c18fe8b7fc9f.png)\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- OS: macOS 10.15.6\r\n- Browser: FireFox\r\n- Version: 80.0.1\r\n\r\n",
